Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.99,0:00:05.35,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}From a different point of view, even an imposing\Nwall blocking your path is just a large door.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.35,0:00:07.06,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We finally figured out the upside-down trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.06,0:00:09.70,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An incomplete novel, and a cornered killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.70,0:00:11.16,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.16,0:00:12.79,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but\Nhas the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.79,0:00:14.67,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.05,0:02:00.26,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}My name is Toshihisa Manda, and I'm a novelist who was locked in a hotel in order to finish a novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.89,0:02:03.14,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I sneaked out of the hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.14,0:02:07.81,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and murdered my disciple\Nand ghostwriter, Kohei Haramoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.73,0:02:11.15,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}After that, I snuck back to the hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.19,0:02:13.94,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}in order to forge an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.94,0:02:15.82,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}While we were playing baseball,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.82,0:02:19.61,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}we lost control of the ball, which went flying into Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.61,0:02:21.91,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then, we went to his room...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.12,0:02:28.87,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...where we found him murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.13,0:02:38.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.76,0:02:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You guys came to get your ball,\Nand when you reached this room,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.10,0:02:46.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you found this man on the floor\Nwith blood around his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.10,0:02:50.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was probably murdered\Nduring an attempted theft.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.39,0:02:54.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the room doesn't look particularly messy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.27,0:02:57.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was somebody he knew!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.03,0:02:58.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.32,0:03:00.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.78,0:03:04.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a sign on the door outside saying Do not enter!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.95,0:03:06.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. So?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.37,0:03:09.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{If a robber saw the sign, they'd know to avoid this room because somebody was inside! – loose match}This means somebody's on the other side of the door writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.12,0:03:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! And if you open the door, you'll get spotted right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.33,0:03:15.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There'd be no way to get behind him without him noticing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.38,0:03:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{If I were an intruder and wanted to murder this man,}If it was me, I'd start making some noise on purpose, and once the victim came out of the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.38,0:03:24.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{I'd wait outside the door with a grin and ambush him.}I'd be waiting for him with the weapon ready to strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.60,0:03:26.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're scary, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.14,0:03:30.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The point is, Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} must've let the killer in himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.73,0:03:33.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was someone he knew... Like this man here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.23,0:03:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did the forensics say was the estimated time of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.07,0:03:40.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roughly two hours ago, around 3pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.65,0:03:42.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were you at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.32,0:03:47.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was locked up in a room at the New Beika Hotel so I could finish my latest novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.53,0:03:51.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The New Beika Hotel isn't far from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.37,0:03:55.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd only take a couple of minutes by car or less than ten minutes by bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.29,0:03:57.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shimaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, were you with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.42,0:04:04.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I was sitting in front of the lifts next to the room where {\i1}Sensei{\i0} was.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.93,0:04:08.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he'd have to pass through there to leave the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.97,0:04:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I don't think {\i1}Sensei's{\i0}\Nthat good at sneaking out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.48,0:04:13.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When did he finish the novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.85,0:04:17.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, geez! Don't tell me you suspect me of murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.86,0:04:20.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no! Just following procedure, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.82,0:04:21.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.40,0:04:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Well, he finished the novel around 4pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.49,0:04:32.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, I looked over it in his hotel room, and took a taxi with him to his home, to talk about his next novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.91,0:04:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.42,0:04:39.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{Do you know of anyone who might have had a grudge against Haramoto-san}Do you know if Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} might have any friends with grudges against him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.80,0:04:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beats me. He was a private person.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.59,0:04:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{We hardly ever talked about anything but work.}He told me he wanted to be a novelist,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.47,0:04:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{He organized my projects.}so I gave him jobs like revising my manuscripts and the like.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.64,0:04:52.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you'll find many of my manuscripts on his computer,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.68,0:04:54.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,including ones I never finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.94,0:04:59.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{Did you hook him up with this house?}A while ago, you mentioned that you're the one who let him live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.15,0:05:04.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I used to live here with my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.86,0:05:08.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it got too small for us, so we built a new house across the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.03,0:05:16.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, my sons have all grown up and my wife has passed on, so I live alone now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.54,0:05:20.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to demolish this house, so I let him live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.13,0:05:24.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This place is pretty clean for a bachelor pad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.67,0:05:28.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A housekeeper comes in once a week...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.05,0:05:29.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.22,0:05:34.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} likes to keep things tidy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.31,0:05:36.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, there's nothing in this drawer but a mirror!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.85,0:05:38.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.06,0:05:41.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:45.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's blood and broken pieces of vase on the mirror...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.61,0:05:47.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...but the middle of the drawer is clean!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.53,0:05:51.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Almost like there was something here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.08,0:05:51.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.62,0:05:55.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the murderer was after the contents of this drawer!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.46,0:05:59.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea what it might be, Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.17,0:06:00.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er... No...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.96,0:06:02.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.17,0:06:04.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, isn't it about time you noticed something {\i1}really{\i0} odd?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.92,0:06:09.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! There's something even stranger about this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.01,0:06:11.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stranger?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.18,0:06:13.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look around this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.60,0:06:14.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the shelves!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.89,0:06:15.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The miniature cars...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.89,0:06:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...the dolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.89,0:06:17.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...the books...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.85,0:06:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're all upside-down!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.40,0:06:22.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The kids are right...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.40,0:06:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.48,0:06:25.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.15,0:06:27.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cat!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.95,0:06:28.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that your cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.91,0:06:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't let your cat run around a crime scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.20,0:06:37.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry... I was so focused on this that I forgot all about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.04,0:06:40.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-Inspector! The back door!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.08,0:06:41.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.71,0:06:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a private residence!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.21,0:06:46.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ichimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.13,0:06:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh... You're here too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.22,0:06:51.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.64,0:06:55.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It wasn't me! I'm just the housekeeper!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.39,0:06:57.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.52,0:06:58.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, do you have any idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.73,0:07:00.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.86,0:07:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh... It's probably one of Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s pranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.90,0:07:07.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pranks?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.36,0:07:11.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. He was always pulling ridiculous pranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.45,0:07:14.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like piling his slippers in a tower...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.95,0:07:18.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...or loosening all the light bulbs in the house so they wouldn't turn on...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.41,0:07:22.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...or leaving video tapes in a row in the hall causing a domino effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.29,0:07:25.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he'd spy on my reaction with a creepy grin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.34,0:07:29.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he'd just look at me with an innocent face while I have to clean everything up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.34,0:07:37.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{You have no idea how many times I got mad at him!}That's why I'm sure this is just more of the same. Because he knew I'd be arriving at this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.60,0:07:40.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What, it's just a prank?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.89,0:07:43.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it makes sense it's a prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.06,0:07:46.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Apparently he was pretty childish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.23,0:07:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sheesh, we thought it was some kind of trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.69,0:07:50.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.28,0:07:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't turn them upside-down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.03,0:07:53.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer did!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.74,0:07:54.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.87,0:07:57.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at those books!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.66,0:08:00.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The covers are crumpled up, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.33,0:08:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoever turned them over did it in a hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.04,0:08:04.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are toy cars with their side mirrors broken off
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.25,0:08:07.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and figurines that have fallen out of their boxes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.17,0:08:11.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was apparently a very important\Ncollection to Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.47,0:08:16.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if he wanted to prank the housekeeper, I'm sure he'd be more careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.14,0:08:19.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. The housekeeper arrived roughly two hours after the estimated time of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.64,0:08:21.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He knew when to expect her, so there wouldn't be any rush to set this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.89,0:08:23.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.27,0:08:27.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would the killer do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.02,0:08:30.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, it was to hide something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.11,0:08:31.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.40,0:08:34.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd stand out if {\i1}one{\i0} thing was turned upside-down...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.15,0:08:38.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...so the murderer turned {\i1}everything{\i0} over to hide it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.03,0:08:42.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er, may I leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.29,0:08:45.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's time I got back to the editorial office.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.21,0:08:48.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can come back once you've finished proofreading, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.88,0:08:51.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I still want to talk about my next book!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.09,0:08:55.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0}, I really don't think it's appropriate to discuss a mystery novel on a day like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.72,0:08:57.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.59,0:09:00.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you wrote period novels...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.35,0:09:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At my age, it's time to try something new.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.56,0:09:05.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{In fact, I've already started working on it!}In fact, I don't have much left to do on this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.14,0:09:08.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, even what's on the shelf seems rather well lined-up...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.94,0:09:11.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah... More than half of them are mystery novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.32,0:09:15.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} loved detective novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.82,0:09:18.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He always said his debut would be with one!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.87,0:09:23.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had such an interesting idea for the detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.66,0:09:27.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Ichimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Did he ask you to bring anything today?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.42,0:09:29.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.96,0:09:33.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used to send you out to shop for things for his collections.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.42,0:09:35.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially when he didn't have time to get out of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.43,0:09:37.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, today...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.76,0:09:39.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted me to call him in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.80,0:09:45.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right! He wanted me to set up a dental appointment for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.77,0:09:46.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.64,0:09:50.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just that when I called him from the hotel earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.48,0:09:52.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...he was telling me how excited he was to complete some set.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.94,0:09:57.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't worry. He was probably talking about one of his absurd collections.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.74,0:09:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You called him today?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.99,0:10:01.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.12,0:10:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I often call him when I'm stuck in work... for a change of pace...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.41,0:10:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did he sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.66,0:10:11.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like his usual self.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.04,0:10:12.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.17,0:10:14.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.96,0:10:17.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you figured out who the killer is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.05,0:10:18.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.22,0:10:20.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murderer didn't hide something by turning things upside-down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.80,0:10:23.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He {\i1}thought{\i0} he could hide it\Nby turning them upside-down!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.23,0:10:31.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer didn't hide something by turning stuff upside-down...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.94,0:10:34.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...but he {\i1}thought{\i0} he'd hide it by turning stuff upside-down?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.48,0:10:38.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To be more exact, he {\i1}thought{\i0} it'd be hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.28,0:10:39.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hidden...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.86,0:10:40.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.70,0:10:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As proof, we have what the killer said to interrupt just before it could come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.91,0:10:47.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.41,0:10:49.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's{\i0} the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.04,0:10:50.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.79,0:10:55.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll come back after proofing this manuscript at the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.46,0:10:57.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, may I go too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.46,0:11:01.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to start preparing for a meeting, and want to drop off my cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.34,0:11:02.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.55,0:11:05.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Feel free to call me if anything comes up, I live right across the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.47,0:11:07.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's making a run for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.68,0:11:09.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Should we let him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.39,0:11:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Your next book will be your first detective novel, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.40,0:11:15.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.98,0:11:20.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to read it! I just love mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.57,0:11:23.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if it's on Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s PC.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.62,0:11:26.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.70,0:11:30.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you cheering him on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.62,0:11:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you gonna corner him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.96,0:11:37.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Knowing you, I'm sure you're up to something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.50,0:11:42.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't it time you wiped that smug grin off your face?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.34,0:11:44.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay! I'll tell you the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.05,0:11:47.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But only if you agree to help!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.18,0:11:48.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.06,0:11:49.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.35,0:11:53.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{I can't believe he has the nerve to plan a meeting with his editor now.}His protegé's murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.81,0:11:56.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and he has the nerve to set up a meeting to talk about a mystery novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.73,0:11:57.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.73,0:12:01.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, what about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.15,0:12:02.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.74,0:12:05.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This toy car is broken!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.20,0:12:08.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, the side mirror has snapped off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.12,0:12:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.33,0:12:15.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like the person who moved the items was in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.08,0:12:17.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.29,0:12:22.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did this to play a prank on the housekeeper, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.38,0:12:26.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. Because he knew she'd be arriving at 5 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.89,0:12:30.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This collection probably wasn't all that important to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.81,0:12:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that novel writer told us...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.98,0:12:37.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...how excited Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was about getting a complete set!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.40,0:12:41.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The question is, what collection did he complete?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.19,0:12:43.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but from those words alone, there's no way to know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.65,0:12:47.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could be talking about cars or figurines or sets of books...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.57,0:12:49.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Complete set?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.33,0:12:51.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In a hurry?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.04,0:12:57.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? You got a cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.54,0:13:00.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nah, it's the cat hair! It's all over this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.96,0:13:02.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cat hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.46,0:13:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nlet his cat run around this room
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.51,0:13:08.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,even while the police were searching the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.01,0:13:10.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No wonder there's so much cat hair!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.68,0:13:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.43,0:13:14.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What makes you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.89,0:13:18.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He came here because he heard something break,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.69,0:13:21.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then saw us entering here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.23,0:13:23.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he followed us in case we were dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.65,0:13:26.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd never bring my kitty into danger like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.45,0:13:28.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if I did, I'd keep him in his carrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.91,0:13:33.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could step on something sharp and hurt himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.08,0:13:34.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.54,0:13:36.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like he let his cat run around on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.75,0:13:39.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let his cat run around on purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.79,0:13:46.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, Detective Yako Hyakki allowed a smile to paint itself upon his harshly closed lips.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.97,0:13:56.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naturally, accepting the investigator's word...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.94,0:14:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is as far as it goes...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.57,0:14:07.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You took longer than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.49,0:14:09.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er, yes, sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.66,0:14:11.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I ran into some trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.53,0:14:17.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well, {\i1}Sensei{\i0}, why don't you tell me about this detective novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.04,0:14:19.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You say you've already started work on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.33,0:14:22.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. In fact, I'm almost to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.67,0:14:24.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just wondering how to wrap it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.92,0:14:28.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, in this murder case,\Nthe detective is the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.80,0:14:29.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.80,0:14:35.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, the story is about an attorney who's murdered at the beginning of the novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.14,0:14:40.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She possesses the body of a friend of hers, a police detective, to solve her own murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.52,0:14:43.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah... That sounds interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.90,0:14:47.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our attorney/detective's\Nname is Yako Hyakki.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.99,0:14:49.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has a ring to it, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.78,0:14:53.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who could it be at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.66,0:14:56.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.87,0:15:00.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but could this wait until after my meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.50,0:15:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We think you can spare us the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.88,0:15:05.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, we've solved the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.59,0:15:07.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Solved the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.63,0:15:08.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.88,0:15:10.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.34,0:15:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who murdered Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.09,0:15:14.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...was {\i1}you{\i0}, Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.85,0:15:18.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.10,0:15:21.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the famous novelist, is a murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.19,0:15:26.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wasn't Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} locked in his hotel room working since the previous night,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.19,0:15:29.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and thus would still be there at 3pm,\Nthe time of the crime?{this could probably be divided}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.65,0:15:34.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The editor, Shimaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, probably wasn't watching the door the whole time,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.53,0:15:39.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he probably snuck out in disguise as a bellhop or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.12,0:15:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he probably took a bicycle or something similar he'd prepared in advance to Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.46,0:15:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In a careless moment, he beat him to death with a vase,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.71,0:15:53.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and rushed back to the hotel to create a perfect alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.26,0:15:55.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there was a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.05,0:15:58.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. The cat you had with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.14,0:16:02.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It ran away from the room where the crime took place to the adjacent room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.94,0:16:06.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You searched the house, but the cat was hiding somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.65,0:16:09.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when you remembered something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.94,0:16:12.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That before you killed Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.74,0:16:15.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he'd mentioned finally having a complete set of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.41,0:16:19.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You live across the street from Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.20,0:16:25.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew that if you left the back door open, the cat would come back to your house when it got hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.08,0:16:32.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But before that, he'd walk all around the house, all over the collection that Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had just finished today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.05,0:16:36.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we found those cat hairs, we'd have proof you'd come to this house today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.26,0:16:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, you and your cat
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.51,0:16:42.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,were supposed to have been locked up working in that hotel room since the night before!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.10,0:16:45.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when you came up with an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.10,0:16:47.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you turned all of his collectibles upside-down,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.56,0:16:52.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then when the housekeeper came in two hours and set everything right,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.07,0:16:54.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she'd knock the cat hair off the items!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.11,0:16:58.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah... But what if the cat hair stayed on anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.87,0:17:00.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't need to fall off!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.87,0:17:04.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He just needed Ichimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to tell the police she'd touched the items!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.75,0:17:10.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cat hair on the floor could've got stuck on the toy cars while she was flipping them back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.13,0:17:15.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why bother to turn\Neverything upside-down?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.59,0:17:18.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not just knock things to the floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.97,0:17:21.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that wouldn't look like a prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.97,0:17:23.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she thought it was the work of a thief,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.89,0:17:27.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she might call the police without touching the crime scene, ruining the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.23,0:17:32.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we went into the room before the housekeeper got there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.61,0:17:36.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! That's why\NManda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was so nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.53,0:17:38.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he had to use his brain a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.32,0:17:41.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} saw us entering that house,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.99,0:17:45.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he hurried over with his cat...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.16,0:17:50.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and let it run around the house so it could get hair on everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.71,0:17:55.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why he got upset when we tried to pick the cat up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.17,0:18:00.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we held the cat until the police came, his plan wouldn't have worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.72,0:18:06.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he still managed to cover up the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.10,0:18:09.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With no proof, he can say you're just making everything up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.52,0:18:12.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but I left a perfect bait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.44,0:18:16.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wonderful deduction, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.82,0:18:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I advise you to become a mystery novelist!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.20,0:18:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But where's the proof? If you don't have any proof, you can't arrest me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.04,0:18:30.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, I'm not the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.46,0:18:34.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I think I'll use that deduction in my next novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.34,0:18:38.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of mystery novels, we found one on Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.63,0:18:42.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An unfinished manuscript\Nstarring a ghost detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.97,0:18:44.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...named Yako Hyakki!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.35,0:18:45.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.60,0:18:51.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We asked Shimaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, your editor, to cooperate with us and wired his clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.02,0:18:54.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We heard you're working on a novel...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.82,0:18:56.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...about a ghost detective with the same name!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.99,0:18:58.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I told you, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.82,0:19:01.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haramoto kept copies of all my rough drafts!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.78,0:19:06.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you wrote that manuscript?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.66,0:19:09.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.12,0:19:14.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To be honest, the children were playing on the computer when they stumbled upon the novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.04,0:19:19.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My men and I read it along with them, hoping it might contain some clue to Haramoto's murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.13,0:19:23.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I have to admit I wasn't sharp enough to guess the ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.64,0:19:26.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe you'd be kind enough to tell me who the murderer in the story is, and the trick that was used.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.81,0:19:29.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.35,0:19:38.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, you wouldn't let us see the CD case with the CD you stole from Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s drawer,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.78,0:19:41.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as that case should still have his blood on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.49,0:19:44.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were reading it just now, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.45,0:19:47.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As after returning from the hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.45,0:19:50.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you found Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body and didn't come back home until now,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.71,0:19:55.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as you were with your editor since then, leaving you with no time to read it beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.38,0:19:58.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And despite that, you were telling Shimaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} the entire story just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.55,0:20:01.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me that boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.42,0:20:04.09,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I can't wait to read it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.09,0:20:06.68,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I wonder if it's on Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s PC.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.68,0:20:12.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Did he push me to read the manuscript right away so I wouldn't have time to hide the disc?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.19,0:20:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That CD and its case...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.48,0:20:16.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're in your house, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.90,0:20:21.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sensei!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.53,0:20:27.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm no {\i1}sensei{\i0} anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.12,0:20:31.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just an old man whose fire went out after his wife's passing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.21,0:20:36.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is, my work over the last two to three years was written by Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.79,0:20:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first I heavily revised his drafts\Nbefore publishing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.67,0:20:46.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then he started complaining\Nabout my revisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.72,0:20:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{He wouldn't let me have any say in what he wrote for me.}And lately, I couldn't find anything\Nwrong with his work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.85,0:20:50.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And finally...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.64,0:20:55.40,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Please... Just stay in the bleachers and let me do my stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.40,0:20:58.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've already passed the torch.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.90,0:21:03.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those words were so depressing and humiliating...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.70,0:21:05.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't forgive him for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.91,0:21:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why did you steal his mystery novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.95,0:21:15.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was overcome with the idea that\NI could write it better than he could.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.79,0:21:18.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.29,0:21:19.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how much I think,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.75,0:21:22.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have no idea who the killer was, or what trick he used.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.34,0:21:27.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I never was cut out to be a mystery writer...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.72,0:22:59.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was the housekeeper's comments who gave you the clue?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.35,0:23:00.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.35,0:23:04.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, when she was trying to tell us about the detective that Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came up with,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.11,0:23:07.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} interrupted her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.07,0:23:09.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when I realized he was trying\Nto steal Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s work!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.57,0:23:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That just leaves one mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.70,0:23:13.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the murderer in the novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.74,0:23:18.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! The complete set\NHaramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.45,0:23:19.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.62,0:23:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was probably talking about his teeth!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.62,0:23:23.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Teeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.42,0:23:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The housekeeper, Ichimura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, said she'd made a dental appointment for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.42,0:23:37.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there was a mirror inside the drawer Haramoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was looking into when Manda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.14,0:23:43.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, among the vase's fragments inside the drawer, there was a dental piece.{might need a proper EN term here}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.31,0:23:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell Inspector Megure about something this important?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.36,0:23:52.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he already knew who the killer was.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.45,0:23:54.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, forensics will tell him that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.91,0:23:58.49,Signs,,0,0,0,,ha
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.91,0:23:58.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.46,0:24:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A death threat?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.42,0:24:14.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The writer was murdered\Nby a character from her novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.68,0:24:16.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer must be trying\Nto confuse the investigators.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.47,0:24:19.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But was that the only objective?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.06,0:24:30.07,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.11,0:24:35.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Sushi ginger.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.16,0:24:36.49,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What kind of fish is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.49,0:24:38.37,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's {\i1}ginger{\i0}, you dummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.49,0:24:38.37,Signs,,0,0,0,,shôga
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.37,0:24:40.12,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You really are hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.37,0:24:40.12,Signs,,0,0,0,,shô ga nai
